00:27:44,731 --> 00:27:47,880
Apparently, all his partners want
to join the meeting,

251
00:27:47,880 --> 00:27:50,260
so they're still trying to coordinate schedules.

252
00:27:52,967 --> 00:27:56,860
Fingers crossed! Hope it all works out.

253
00:27:56,860 --> 00:27:59,053
Should we make a vow at a shrine or something?

254
00:27:59,053 --> 00:28:02,060
Sure, but write it down
so we know what to make offerings for later.

255
00:28:02,060 --> 00:28:05,333
I think our project is really promising.
We've got a good shot.

256
00:28:05,333 --> 00:28:09,385
Might just need to tweak a few terms.

257
00:28:10,120 --> 00:28:12,432
- We're gonna be rich!
- Rich!

258
00:28:20,900 --> 00:28:24,738
[Grandma Jan's Restaurant]

259
00:28:24,738 --> 00:28:30,820
Mom, We should sell our land.

260
00:28:30,820 --> 00:28:33,953
Even half of it would help.

261
00:28:33,953 --> 00:28:37,040
I can't handle this anymore.

262
00:28:37,040 --> 00:28:44,407
We spend tens of thousands a year
just maintaining it.

263
00:28:44,407 --> 00:28:53,148
Ji's been working so hard
just to send money for living expenses.

264
00:28:55,280 --> 00:28:57,727
Mom.

265
00:28:57,727 --> 00:29:00,187
Did you hear me?

266
00:29:00,187 --> 00:29:02,367
I heard.

267
00:29:02,367 --> 00:29:05,327
I just don't want to sell.

268
00:29:05,327 --> 00:29:10,633
If I said I was waiting to die first,
I'd feel bad.

269
00:29:10,633 --> 00:29:13,693
But I don't know when I'll die.

270
00:29:13,693 --> 00:29:18,853
Mom, No one wants you to die.

271
00:29:18,853 --> 00:29:22,767
We just want what's best for everyone.

272
00:29:24,500 --> 00:29:27,787
We can keep 5 rai for ourselves.

273
00:29:27,787 --> 00:29:30,687
We're not asking you to sell it all.

274
00:29:30,687 --> 00:29:33,020
Please, Mom.

275
00:29:33,020 --> 00:29:34,514
Please?

276
00:29:44,420 --> 00:29:46,087
<i>Hello, Grandma.</i>

277
00:29:46,087 --> 00:29:48,645
When are you coming back?

278
00:29:49,573 --> 00:29:51,807
Are you okay? Are you not feeling well?

279
00:29:51,807 --> 00:29:56,569
Your mom wants to sell the land again.

280
00:29:56,569 --> 00:29:58,073
And what do you think, Grandma?

281
00:29:58,073 --> 00:30:00,893
<i>I won't sell. I don't want to.</i>

282
00:30:00,893 --> 00:30:08,040
Will you be okay if I don't sell?
Can you wait until I die?

283
00:30:08,040 --> 00:30:10,040
Don't say that, Grandma.
If you don't want to sell, then don't.

284
00:30:10,040 --> 00:30:13,227
I'll support you no matter what.

285
00:30:13,227 --> 00:30:16,013
<i>This land is all we've got.</i>

286
00:30:16,013 --> 00:30:18,580
Money runs out.

287
00:30:18,580 --> 00:30:22,627
I'm just worried
you kids won't have anything to live on.

288
00:30:22,627 --> 00:30:27,100
Grandma, take it easy.
I'll come see you tomorrow and we'll talk.

289
00:30:27,100 --> 00:30:30,007
I'll also talk to Mom for you. Okay?

290
00:30:31,340 --> 00:30:32,896
Okay.

291
00:30:45,500 --> 00:30:47,399
[Food Retreats]

292
00:30:52,880 --> 00:30:56,580
- Hello?
- I'm planning to go home tomorrow.

293
00:30:56,580 --> 00:30:59,880
What? So sudden? Is something wrong?

294
00:30:59,880 --> 00:31:03,100
Yeah, my mom and grandma are fighting again.

295
00:31:03,100 --> 00:31:06,240
Why? Does your mom want to sell the land?

296
00:31:06,240 --> 00:31:09,720
Yeah. She wants to, but Grandma refuses.

297
00:31:09,720 --> 00:31:12,787
I need to go talk to them
and figure out what's really going on.

298
00:31:12,787 --> 00:31:15,340
If you need to talk about it, just call me, okay?

299
00:31:15,340 --> 00:31:16,860
Thanks so much.

300
00:31:16,860 --> 00:31:19,107
Where are you now? What time are you getting home?

301
00:31:19,107 --> 00:31:20,220
At the office.

302
00:31:20,220 --> 00:31:23,280
Will probably stay late.
I have a presentation the day after tomorrow.

303
00:31:23,280 --> 00:31:25,660
Okay. Hang in there. Good luck!

304
00:31:25,660 --> 00:31:27,180
And don't stay up too late.

305
00:31:27,180 --> 00:31:30,040
If you're too tired to drive back, let me know.
I'll come get you, okay?

306
00:31:30,040 --> 00:31:31,867
Okay. Bye.

307
00:31:31,867 --> 00:31:33,693
<i>Bye-bye.</i>

308
00:31:58,813 --> 00:32:01,647
[Grandma Jan's Restaurant]

309
00:32:01,647 --> 00:32:04,313
Oh, Ji. What brings you here, son?

310
00:32:04,313 --> 00:32:08,707
- Hello.
- Didn't even tell me you were coming again.

311
00:32:12,833 --> 00:32:16,487
Let me guess, Grandma called you, didn't she?

312
00:32:16,487 --> 00:32:18,407
- Correct.
- See?

313
00:32:18,407 --> 00:32:21,599
When it comes to that topic, it's untouchable.

314
00:32:21,599 --> 00:32:23,947
Can't even mention it.

315
00:32:23,947 --> 00:32:28,470
You know she can't talk about it,
yet still bring it up with Grandma again.

316
00:32:28,470 --> 00:32:31,149
Come on, come sit down first, dear.

317
00:32:33,940 --> 00:32:38,493
I really can't handle it anymore, Ji.
It's too much.

318
00:32:38,493 --> 00:32:42,663
With that much land,
how am I supposed to manage it alone?

319
00:32:44,413 --> 00:32:47,880
So, what are you planning to do?

320
00:32:47,880 --> 00:32:50,833
Tell Grandma you're moving back here?

321
00:32:50,833 --> 00:32:52,953
She keeps waiting and waiting,

322
00:32:52,953 --> 00:32:57,367
even set the land aside,
not letting anyone touch it.

323
00:32:57,367 --> 00:33:02,267
Tell me honestly, are you really moving back here?

324
00:33:02,267 --> 00:33:06,440
You're coming back
just to sell random stuff at home like that?

325
00:33:06,440 --> 00:33:09,520
If I had to come back for real, I would, Mom.

326
00:33:09,520 --> 00:33:11,820
Sure, it's possible.

327
00:33:11,820 --> 00:33:15,560
But what are you going to do?

328
00:33:15,560 --> 00:33:19,620
Start a home stay? That takes a lot of capital.

329
00:33:19,620 --> 00:33:24,778
And if it's not well done or doesn't look good,
no one will come.

330
00:33:25,913 --> 00:33:31,682
And if you want to open a coffee shop,
those are everywhere already.

331
00:33:32,667 --> 00:33:38,413
I honestly want to know
how many cups of coffee can one drink in a day?

332
00:33:38,413 --> 00:33:41,773
Mom, listen.

333
00:33:41,773 --> 00:33:47,067
I've saved up a good chunk of money.
It's enough to start something.

334
00:33:47,067 --> 00:33:50,653
But I have to think very carefully
about what to do.

335
00:33:50,653 --> 00:33:55,593
Give me just a little time.
This is all I've got. If I use it up, that's it.

336
00:33:55,593 --> 00:33:58,880
And I don't think I'll ever be able
to earn this kind of money again.

337
00:33:58,880 --> 00:34:01,865
So I have to be smart about it.

338
00:34:16,679 --> 00:34:18,307
Ji.

339
00:34:18,307 --> 00:34:21,160
Can I ask you something, dear?

340
00:34:26,727 --> 00:34:30,027
You said you were working in Bangkok.

341
00:34:31,353 --> 00:34:33,868
What exactly were you doing?

342
00:34:50,673 --> 00:34:54,180
Grandpa Win's son,
who also went to work in Bangkok,

343
00:34:54,180 --> 00:34:56,923
showed me this video.

344
00:35:17,220 --> 00:35:21,573
I've been trying to hide it from Grandma.

345
00:35:21,573 --> 00:35:24,868
But the neighbors keep talking.

346
00:35:27,913 --> 00:35:30,196
They're saying...

347
00:35:32,980 --> 00:35:36,423
Did you go into prostitution in Bangkok, Ji?

348
00:35:59,517 --> 00:36:02,360
It was a bar where women go to hang out, Mom.

349
00:36:03,360 --> 00:36:07,160
I was just entertaining them.
Encouraging them to drink.

350
00:36:07,160 --> 00:36:11,522
Like those beer-promotion girls at pubs,
that's all.

351
00:36:14,727 --> 00:36:19,504
But Ji, did you really do
what the villagers are saying you did?

352
00:36:27,000 --> 00:36:29,973
The reason I want to sell the land is...

353
00:36:30,893 --> 00:36:34,433
if we have money, we can move somewhere else.

354
00:36:34,433 --> 00:36:37,983
We don't have to sit here
and hear people talk about us.

355
00:36:39,733 --> 00:36:43,227
So we're running away? Is that it?

356
00:36:43,227 --> 00:36:45,374
It's not like that.

357
00:36:46,207 --> 00:36:50,120
And besides, if we're not going to do anything
with the land,

358
00:36:50,120 --> 00:36:53,392
then we might as well sell it.

359
00:36:58,280 --> 00:36:59,413
If we have money,

360
00:36:59,413 --> 00:37:04,241
no matter who we were or what we did,
people will shut up.

361
00:37:05,180 --> 00:37:07,562
I'm not ashamed of you, Ji.

362
00:37:09,207 --> 00:37:12,726
I'm just worried about you.

363
00:37:13,753 --> 00:37:19,980
If there's an easier path,
then maybe we should take it.

364
00:37:19,980 --> 00:37:22,293
So you don't have to struggle.

365
00:38:39,093 --> 00:38:41,072
Hello everyone.

366
00:38:41,887 --> 00:38:44,127
- Hi there.
- Good to see you.

367
00:38:47,031 --> 00:38:49,070
Hi.

368
00:38:49,070 --> 00:38:50,671
Hello.

369
00:38:55,467 --> 00:38:57,000
Hello everyone.

370
00:38:57,000 --> 00:38:58,700
Hi, Pitcha.

371
00:38:58,700 --> 00:39:03,047
I'd like to introduce the partners
who'll be listening to your pitch today.

372
00:39:03,047 --> 00:39:06,473
This is Mr. Boy, Ms. Asira, and Mr. Nut.

373
00:39:06,473 --> 00:39:08,817
Hello again, everyone.

374
00:39:09,440 --> 00:39:10,520
Are you ready?

375
00:39:10,520 --> 00:39:12,514
I'm ready, just a little nervous.

376
00:39:12,514 --> 00:39:16,213
This is Ms. Goi, my assistant presenter today.

377
00:39:16,213 --> 00:39:18,600
Shall we get started?

378
00:39:18,600 --> 00:39:20,283
Please go ahead.

379
00:39:22,860 --> 00:39:24,080
[Wellness Center Therapy]

380
00:39:24,080 --> 00:39:27,240
Community-based wellness,
focusing on physical and mental health,

381
00:39:27,240 --> 00:39:30,671
is trending among the younger generation.

382
00:39:47,475 --> 00:39:50,036
[Food Retreats]

383
00:39:50,940 --> 00:39:53,752
Finally, thank you all
[Thank You]

384
00:39:53,752 --> 00:39:58,200
for supporting this kind of meaningful project.

385
00:40:10,020 --> 00:40:13,993
Very informative, Pitcha.
The project is very interesting.

386
00:40:13,993 --> 00:40:15,940
There might be a few small concerns,

387
00:40:15,940 --> 00:40:19,169
so I'm sure there'll be some questions
from everyone.

388
00:40:19,860 --> 00:40:23,100
Let me move on to the next section.

389
00:40:23,100 --> 00:40:27,127
I'd like to invite our special advisor
for this project.

390
00:40:27,127 --> 00:40:28,870
Please welcome...

391
00:41:03,993 --> 00:41:07,807
Hello, Ms. Pitcha.

392
00:41:16,920 --> 00:41:23,327
This is Ms. Anita, a renowned expert
in land investment and real estate.

393
00:41:23,327 --> 00:41:25,219
Please sit down.

394
00:41:29,233 --> 00:41:31,818
- Hello.
- Hello.

395
00:41:39,315 --> 00:41:41,623
I'd like a word.

396
00:41:43,968 --> 00:41:46,685
I can wait. Go ahead.

397
00:41:57,493 --> 00:42:00,353
You never told me about Anita.

398
00:42:00,353 --> 00:42:03,320
True, but does it really matter?

399
00:42:03,320 --> 00:42:05,700
Whether I told you or not,
whether she's here or not,

400
00:42:05,700 --> 00:42:07,920
you'd have to pitch this project anyway.

401
00:42:07,920 --> 00:42:10,820
And honestly, having her here to help
patch the gaps in the proposal

402
00:42:10,820 --> 00:42:12,920
might actually benefit you.

403
00:42:12,920 --> 00:42:15,580
She already owns land, and she's an investor.

404
00:42:15,580 --> 00:42:17,449
What if she learns everything
and goes off to do it herself?

405
00:42:17,449 --> 00:42:22,107
Come on, she's got a name in this industry.
She wouldn't do that.

406
00:42:22,107 --> 00:42:26,247
Plus, I've got an entire board
who can confirm that this is your project.

407
00:42:26,247 --> 00:42:28,313
It's not that complicated.

408
00:42:28,313 --> 00:42:32,273
If it's not complicated,
then why didn't you tell me she'd be here?

409
00:42:32,273 --> 00:42:34,860
Why did you let her Zoom in from another room?

410
00:42:34,860 --> 00:42:39,457
If there's nothing suspicious,
why didn't she just join like everyone else?

411
00:42:40,761 --> 00:42:44,267
You had me pitch the project in front of her
without telling me.

412
00:42:44,267 --> 00:42:47,761
You let her listen to my full presentation first.

413
00:42:48,813 --> 00:42:51,277
You really are an asshole.

414
00:42:57,860 --> 00:43:01,240
Alright, sorry for the wait.

415
00:43:01,240 --> 00:43:05,084
I just had to check a few things with Mr. Wasu.

416
00:43:10,933 --> 00:43:18,393
Now, Ms. Anita,
please feel free to comment on my project.

417
00:43:18,393 --> 00:43:22,368
Let me just record this in case I miss anything.

418
00:43:25,493 --> 00:43:27,393
It's a good project.

419
00:43:27,393 --> 00:43:30,927
Wellness is a rising trend globally.

420
00:43:30,927 --> 00:43:36,380
In Bali, there are similar projects
that earn high returns every year.

421
00:43:36,380 --> 00:43:40,433
There's nothing wrong, except...

422
00:43:40,433 --> 00:43:44,264
The land you proposed? Not worth it.

423
00:43:45,100 --> 00:43:51,936
It's only a few rai, requires a high investment,
and you can't sustain long-term gains from it.

424
00:43:52,793 --> 00:43:58,280
Honestly, Pitcha has access to
far more promising land.

425
00:43:58,280 --> 00:44:00,717
The one she haven't shown you yet.

426
00:44:01,960 --> 00:44:07,069
The land that only Wasu and I know about.

427
00:44:12,113 --> 00:44:15,006
What exactly did you two agree on?

428
00:44:15,749 --> 00:44:19,127
My friends in China mention you often.

429
00:44:19,127 --> 00:44:22,014
They say you're a very promising newcomer.

430
00:44:22,746 --> 00:44:27,077
If you're saying that,
then I'll take it as a compliment.

431
00:44:28,680 --> 00:44:31,393
Let's get to the point.

432
00:44:31,393 --> 00:44:34,967
I heard you're developing a new project
with Pitcha.

433
00:44:34,967 --> 00:44:38,447
Sorry, I can't remember the name of her company.

434
00:44:38,447 --> 00:44:42,373
I just want to know do you already
have a primary investor for this project,

435
00:44:42,373 --> 00:44:45,347
or are you still open to partners?

436
00:44:45,347 --> 00:44:51,207
Because my friends and I are interested
in both your company and Pitcha's idea.

437
00:44:51,207 --> 00:44:54,171
She and I have worked together before.

438
00:44:54,827 --> 00:44:58,163
We'd definitely welcome a partner like you.

439
00:44:58,960 --> 00:45:02,400
Great. In that case...

440
00:45:02,400 --> 00:45:06,440
Let me share my investment conditions first.

441
00:45:06,440 --> 00:45:09,716
Of course, please go ahead.

442
00:45:11,403 --> 00:45:17,583
I want final decision-making power
over this project.

443
00:45:19,987 --> 00:45:22,940
And I want the land in Nan.

444
00:45:26,207 --> 00:45:28,779
The one you know exactly where it is.

445
00:45:32,033 --> 00:45:35,896
You're pressuring me
to hand over Jira's land to you.

446
00:45:36,933 --> 00:45:39,180
The return is enormous.

447
00:45:39,180 --> 00:45:43,500
Before you answer, go run the numbers.
